Thank you so much for hanging out with me and Ry on our new podcast! Shortly after launching, we jumped to the number one ranking in kids and family category and we just passed 50,000 downloads. These numbers don’t matter, but they make Ryan and I so happy because that means that you’re taking time to write your own story and join us in figuring out how you can level up as a parent and as a partner. 

We have so many more amazing episodes planned for you, this is just the beginning! Thank you for being here, and supporting us every step of the way - we’re having so much fun sharing our experiences with you and your feedback is motivating us to keep showing up! 

Tell us below in the comments, what episode have you enjoyed the most? And, what would you like to hear more about?

Merry Christmas from the Tripp’s 🎁

I remember a time I was sitting on the edge of our bed after a long heartbreaking ER shift talking to Ry about feeling stuck, wondering if we were making the very most of the precious time we have here together. Now a handful years later, after a lot of sacrifice, tears, big choices, and courage …  I sit on the edge of my bed with a lap full of kids looking at Ry with a big ol’ lump in my throats and tears in my eyes — we LIVED all 365 days this past year and we did it together!

I’m just so dang grateful. 🥹😭

We have learned that this life is as big and beautiful as you make it, that kids are as amazing as you give them the opportunity to be, that the hardest things in life are often the very best, that money returns but time doesn’t, and ultimately that you will never regret making the dang most of it while you’ve got it. Whatever it is that you want out of this year, don’t let the scary or the hard stop you, we say go for it — love some of your biggest cheerleaders. 🫶🏻
Reminder: try something new with your spouse this year ⛷️
Family man. Golfer. Guinness Record Holder
